cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification using deep transfer learning, which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an unsupervised domain adaptation method, which involves learning domain-invariant features, and this is a common problem in machine learning (ML) research, particularly in the sub-field of transfer learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses deep neural networks to perform feature extraction and classification, which falls under the sub-field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its method on a benchmark dataset for person re-identification (Market-1501), which is a common dataset used in multimedia (MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses related work on adversarial attacks and defenses, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR).
